SUMMARIZER="G">

President Bush at an East Room reception congratulated the San Francisco 49ers on their 20-16 
Super Bowl victory.  Surrounded by 49ers, Bush said they rewrote the record books and raised 
football to a new level of excellence.  Quarterback Joe Montana said being invited to the White 
House "meant a lot to us all... Not very often do I get to see these guys in ties."

Bush was presented with autographed footballs by Montana and wide receiver Jerry Rice, who 
won the game's MVP award; a Super Bowl ring by team owner Danny DeBartolo; and a 49ers 
jogging outfit by Coach Bill Walsh.</SUM>

<SUM
