The Los Angeles Sports Council, in a bid to bring Super Bowl XXVII to the Rose Bowl in 1993, 
will offer the stadium rent free to the National Football League along with all income from 
concessions and sales of novelty items.  The Council selected the Rose Bowl because it has 
103,083 seats.  Under a joint agreement, Anaheim Stadium and the Coliseum did not submit bids 
but they would share in the revenues if Pasadena gets the game.  The share is still being 
negotiated.  One plan calls for the Rose Bowl to receive 75% of the proceeds; the other two 
sharing 25%.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d096"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="SJMN91-06025282"
SELECTOR="C"
SUMMARIZER="G">

Henry Carley, president of Tampa's local chapter of the NAACP, is co-chairman of one of the 
feature events of Super Bowl week, the Bambaleo Parade, an extravaganza with marching bands, 
a street festival, and floats.  Carley's efforts calmed a racial dispute over Tampa's traditional 
white-dominated Gasparilla Parade, which had to be cancelled.

The Super Bowl Task Force this year named two black men to head a community-relations 
committee.  Carley said there is much more involvement this time, black and white, than the 
1984 event.  There will be an event saluting black sports legends.  Several minority-owned 
businesses won lucrative contracts with the NFL.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d096"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="SJMN91-06025182"
SELECTOR="C"
SUMMARIZER="G">

Super Bowl XXV will kickoff in Tampa Stadium, Tampa, Florida.  Winners receive $36,000 per 
man.  The losers receive $18,000 per man.  If there is overtime because of a tie, the team scoring 
first will win.   The overtime play will be in 15-minute periods.

The winning team will receive permanent possession of the Vince Lombardi Trophy, named 
after the late coach Vince Lombardi of the two-time Super Bowl champion Green Bay Packers.  
The trophy, valued at $10,000, is a regulation silver football mounted in a kicking position on a 
pyramid-like stand of three concave sides and is 20.75 inches high.</SUM>
